doc.field: Built of red sandstone, Agra Fort combines Hindu and Islamic architecture. Agra Fort is a UNESCO World Heritage site located in Agra near the famous Taj Mahal. This walled cityfort was fortified at various stages by the Mughal emporors Humayun, Akbar, Jehangir, Shah Jahan and Aurangzeb.
